author: bfoster
msg: - created a DatabaseFactory that allows a Database object to be linked to a remote object through rmi or create a local DatabaseServer (non-rmi).  This was done for cases where rmi is not desired.

- currently the Crawler is in the middle of integration. . .this is not a running version. . .use previous code rev if working code is desired. . .code was solely committed to preserve changes from being lost.  Hopefully in the next rev following this commit, the Crawler will again be functional.

author: bfoster
msg: Made changes to Ingester and to ProductCrawler's usage of Ingesters

- ProductCrawler now can accept any Ingester which controls how communication with a back end database is controlled.  Currently there are now two Ingesters: StdIngester and CacheIngester.  CacheIngester still communicates with the file manager in the same way as StdIngester however it keeps a local cache of ingested files so that queries to the file manager are limited.
